   \begin{pmatrix}f(n)\\ f(n+1)\end{pmatrix}=   A^n\cdot\begin{pmatrix}f(0)\\ f(1)\end{pmatrix}   \qquad\text{where $A=\begin{pmatrix}0&1\\\ 1&1\end{pmatrix}$ so that $A^n=\begin{pmatrix}F_{n-1}&F_n \\ F_n& F_{n+1}\end{pmatrix}$} 
   \begin{pmatrix}f(0)\\ f(1)\end{pmatrix}=   A^{-n}\cdot\begin{pmatrix}f(n)\\ f(n+1)\end{pmatrix}   \qquad\text{where $A^{-n}=(-1)^n\begin{pmatrix}F_{n+1}&-F_n \\\ -F_n& F_{n-1}\end{pmatrix}$.} 
